     DESCRIPTION
                 ls -list the current directory contents

RID1 :Name your execute as my_ls.c    ex: gcc -o my_ls filename.c

RID2 :Execute my_ls without parameters check list directory or current directory.

RID3 :Execute my_ls with one argument to  pass argument is a directory or not

RID4 :Execute my_ls with one argument  to read the directory and display the list of files directory

RID5 :Close the dir.
